review: the market has a unique variety of produce ranging from fresh fish to deep fried chicken  try your best to avoid the market on saturdays as it is super crowded with people lining up just to purchase from stalls  it s a unique experience to see the local delights on offer  and it is not watered down for tourists

review: great market with all the local selections available at a reasonable cost  we had the squid with some rice stuffing inside which tasted perfect  it costed 10k won  we also bought a steam cake with had a long queue and it costed 3 5k won  the chicken box was the number one rating and it cost 18k won  seriously  that box was good enough to feed 4 paxes   the prawn fritters were very good too  at least 1k won each   infact they also had one with a real crab legs  also 1k won each

name: D. Pops
review: amazing central market in the heart of sokcho  there are all kinds of foods  especially seafood and it is all delicious  the place is one huge labrynth of eateries

name: Jack
review: overall a great market for some genuine korean food at a decent price  there is a lot of variety and countless shops to choose from  that said  there are some things to look out for  first  a lot of the shops have a propensity to precook their food then reheat it when you purchase it  or not at all  it s a good idea to insist on the freshly made ones and definitely do not buy anything that s turned stone cold or looks like it sat around all day  the fried foods are a prime example of this  second  if you are adventurous then you should venture into a seafood shop where they have fresh live seafood on display out front  the best ones are in the basement of a building  you ll know by walking down some stairs past the restrooms  there s a huge sprawling area filled with koreans eating fresh seafood and sitting at low tables  to eat here  you ll have to negotiate the price of some amount of seafood you ll pick from the tanks  i repeat  you must negotiate the price of the seafood lower and don t ever let them lead you to believe the free  service  food they give you is actually worth anything  good luck

review: not too crowded on weekdays but crowded on weekends especially at mealtimes  lots of quality street food  the  chicken  is a must in the market and  not to be missed for fish fans  the famous  fish market  in the basement where you can take away  we choose the fish and it is prepared in sashimi  or eat on the spot to taste a stew of fresh fish      pas trop de monde en semaine mais blind  le week end surtout a l heure du repas  beaucoup de street food de qualit   le   chicken   est un must du march  et    ne pas manquer pour les fans de poisson  le fameux   fish market   au sous sol o  vous pourrez prendre   emporter  on choisit le poisson et il est pr par  en sashimi  ou manger sur place pour go ter un rago t de poisson frais

name: weng i loi
review: there are many seafood restaurants on both sides of the clean market  and the corridor fish tanks are filled with a variety of seafood  we saw a fish with a lot of black markings  under the question  it turned out to be a rare flower goldfish  hk 1500  and the sashimi hot pot is delicious  there are a lot of seagulls on the shore  and it s super cute  the seafood restaurant can buy dried bonito and kelp at a reasonable price                                                                               1500

name: wy Kwok
review: all kinds of seafood are available  and fresh live crabs are even better  they can be steamed and cut to make it easy for you to eat  the meat is sweet and unbeatable  the price is reasonable

name: Yen Ting Shih
review: seafood and fresh seafood special local snacks in the market must eat fried chicken fried shrimp egg fried squid rice sausage kimchi pancake
